\fBcmake_minimum_required()\fP \%<#\:command:cmake_minimum_required> or \fBcmake_policy()\fP \%<#\:command:cmake_policy>\&.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Conditionally linked imported targets with missing include directories.
.sp
CMake 2.8.11 introduced introduced the concept of
\fBINTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES>, and a check at cmake time that the
entries in the \fBINTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES> of an \fBIMPORTED\fP
target actually exist.  CMake 2.8.11 also introduced generator expression
support in the \fBtarget_link_libraries()\fP \%<#\:command:target_link_libraries> command.  However, if an
imported target is linked as a result of a generator expression evaluation, the
entries in the \fBINTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES> of that target were not
checked for existence as they should be.
.sp
The \fBOLD\fP behavior of this policy is to report a warning if an entry in
the \fBINTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES> of a generator\-expression
conditionally linked \fBIMPORTED\fP target does not exist.
.sp
The \fBNEW\fP behavior of this policy is to report an error if an entry in
the \fBINTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES\fP \%<#\:prop_tgt:INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES> of a generator\-expression
conditionally linked \fBIMPORTED\fP target does not exist.
.sp
This policy was introduced in CMake version 3.0\&.
Prior to removal in CMake version 4.0, it could be
set by \fBcmake_policy()\fP \%<#\:command:cmake_policy> or \fBcmake_minimum_required()\fP \%<#\:command:cmake_minimum_required>\&.
If it was not set, CMake warned, and used \fBOLD\fP behavior.
.SS CMP0026
.sp
\fBWarning:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
The \fBOLD\fP behavior of this policy was removed
in CMake version 4.0\&.
