.sp
Disallow include export result.
.sp
CMake 2.8.12 and lower allowed use of the \fBinclude()\fP \%<#\:command:include> command with the
result of the \fBexport()\fP \%<#\:command:export> command.  This relies on the assumption that
the \fBexport()\fP \%<#\:command:export> command has an immediate effect at configure\-time during
a cmake run.  Certain properties of targets are not fully determined
until later at generate\-time, such as the link language and complete
list of link libraries.  Future refactoring will change the effect of
the \fBexport()\fP \%<#\:command:export> command to be executed at generate\-time.  Use \fBALIAS\fP
targets instead in cases where the goal is to refer to targets by
another name.
.sp
The \fBOLD\fP behavior for this policy is to allow including the result of
an \fBexport()\fP \%<#\:command:export> command.  The \fBNEW\fP behavior for this policy is not to
allow including the result of an \fBexport()\fP \%<#\:command:export> command.
.sp
This policy was introduced in CMake version 3.0\&.
Prior to removal in CMake version 4.0, it could be
set by \fBcmake_policy()\fP \%<#\:command:cmake_policy> or \fBcmake_minimum_required()\fP \%<#\:command:cmake_minimum_required>\&.
If it was not set, CMake warned, and used \fBOLD\fP behavior.
.SS Policies Introduced by CMake 2.8, Removed by CMake 4.0
.SS CMP0023
.sp
